divs: Sighting DetailsI was letting the dog out of my hourse around 9:30PM when a very bright star (?) caught my eye, I got the binoculars and it was pulsating colors of blue to red to orange to gold. It was stationary in the North for about half an hour then slowly moved to the East. I did take a picture with my iPhone but I can't see anything on the picture, maybe if it was enhanced.
Summary: Pulsating lights, stationary then moved east, extremely bright colors
